						<summary>

						<p>On the inner wall of the <hi rend="italic">gōpura</hi> of the Uttara-Raṅganāthasvāmin temple, right of entrance.</p>						

						<p>Veṅkaṭapati II, 1638 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1559, Bahudhānya, Āśvīja ba. 3.</hi> If the Śaka year quoted is a mistake for 1560, the details correspond to <hi rend="bold">1638 A.D., October 15, (Monday).</hi></p>						

						<p>It seems to record some gift, probably of land, made by the king to Koṇiki Rāmaliṅgam for some service in the temple of Pallikoṇḍa-Raṅganāthasvāmin.</p>						

						</summary>
